 All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential candidate, Bola Tinubu, has opened the South-West office for his presidential campaign in Akure, Ondo State on Saturday. The Ondo State APC shared photos from the event on their Twitter handle, stating that the opening of the office was done after Tinubu attended the presidential rally that held in the city.  The photos were captioned, “Asiwaju #officialABAT has inaugurated the APC Southwest Campaign office in Akure immediately after the presidential rally. Asiwaju Tinubu was led to the campaign office by Governor #RotimiAkeredolu, SAN, CON.” 